title: For Sale:  Model 1874 .45-110 45 2 7/8' Single Shot Rifle
location: south Carolina, South Carolina, United States
postcontent:
LSB#: 120821RS04

Make: Shiloh Sharps (Farmingdale NY)

Model: Model 1874 Business Rifle

Serial Number: 3842

Year of Manufacture: Ca. 1980's, 1990's

Caliber: .45-110 WCF, .45 2 7/8"

Action Type: Single Shot, Falling Block

Markings: The top of the barrel is marked "Old Reliable / Shiloh Rifle Mfg. Co. / Caliber 45 / 2 7/8". The left side of the frame is marked "Shiloh rifle Mfg. Co. / Farmingdale N.Y.". The top of the frame is marked "3842".

Barrel Length: 30"

Sights / Optics: This rifle is mounted with a dovetail set front blade, and a screwed on two position sliding rear ladder flip sight. The upper tang is drilled and tapped for a tang sight.

Stock Configuration & Condition: The stocks are oil finished smooth wood. There is an imperfection at the underside of the forearm, at the right side and near the tip. The upper edges of the forearm also show wear and depressions. Most of the stock wear is at the toe and there is scattered dings and marks elsewhere on the stock. The LOP measures about 13 3/4" to the front trigger. The stocks rate in about Fine overall condition.

Type of Finish: Blue / Case Color Hardened

Finish Originality: Factory Original

Bore Condition: The bore is bright, with some fouling that will clean and the rifling is sharp. There is no pitting or erosion.

Overall Condition: This rifle retains about 92% of its metal finish. The frame shows great colors with very little thinning or muting. The tip of the hammer has thinned a bit from use. The barrel shows very little wear, just some thinning at the muzzle. The upper right barrel edge, about 4" from the muzzle shows a ding. There are only one or two other marks on the barrel. The upper tang shows slight marking from a tang sight. The Screw heads are sharp. The markings are crisp. Overall, this rifle rates in about Excellent condition.

Mechanics: The action functions as designed, as do the set triggers. We have not fired this rifle.

Box, Paperwork & Accessories: None

Our Assessment: This is a relatively rare Shiloh Sharps (.45-110) in very nice condition - with a great bore. This is the ultimate long range sharps rifle, and very few modern made guns have risen to the status of collectibilty as Shiloh's ever have. For cowboy action long range shooting, for western re-enactments, for playing Quigley, or for an investment, this rifle is the tops. Shiloh quality is legendary - especiall the Farmingdale guns. There is a long wait on new Shilohs. Don’t let this beautiful rifle get away.

Smith & Wesson combined a Scandium alloy frame to build the strongest, and lightest weight .357 Magnum revolver made. The result is maximum power in a small, lightweight, easy-to-carry package. Scandium alloy is used for small, medium, and large frame revolvers. Smith & Wesson's lightest and strongest revolvers deliver dependable power every time.

I purchased this firearm new from dealer about a month ago for concealed carry. I've now decided I want an FNP-45 Tactical with Trijicon RMR and SilencerCo Osprey suppressor, which will run me $2,500-3,000. I already have too many carry guns so this one's gotta go to help get down the cost of my new tactical .45 investment.

This is an excellent firearm, great for carry and packs a hell of a punch! I've only had it at the range a couple times (50-60 rounds maybe, factory only, no hand loads). This gun is not even broke in yet and will continue to fire tens of thousands of more rounds before any maintenance will need to be done. You also will enjoy the flexibility of being able to shoot a small .38 caliber with much more manageable recoil. You can essentially fire 3 calibers in one gun by selecting to use .38, .38 +P, or the devastating .357 Magnum.

It's hard to beat the stopping power of the .357 magnum, especially when running critical defense hollow points. A revolver will never let you down. No jamming to worry about or cycling a semi automatic action in case of a bad round/ftf. When my life is depending on it, I only carry revolvers for this reason. When the adrenaline hits and fine motor control drops out, all you have to worry about is focusing on the front sight and pulling the trigger.

Comes in original hard case, with all factory accessories, factory test rounds, gun lock and I even have the original grips if you don't like the Crimson Trace Lasergrips or desire the smaller footprint you get from the original grips. This is a $1,129.00 value direct from S&W (approx. $1,215.93 after tax), and for only $850.00 you are getting it at less than 70% the retail price after tax for a gun that is in better than 90% condition.

title: For Sale:  DS Arms SA58 18" Carbine Like New
postcontent:
Up for sale is a DS Arms SA58 18” Carbine. Model number SA58C18RL. I purchased this rifle this year, and it has had 260 rounds through it. I broke in the barrel according to DSA’s website. This rifle is in excellent condition, and has been cleaned after every trip to the range. The only signs of wear are where the optics are mounted and around the ejection port which is typical for this type of firearm. I have been around quite a few FAL’s which why I got this beast.  Unless you spend the money for an all original  pre-ban or a custom build, this is the best FAL on the market.  The fit and finish of the DSA is second to none. This is truly an awesome rifle, and the FAL is a battle proven platform. I hate to part with it but I have other financial interest that takes precedence at this point.

This is DSA’s 18” Carbine. It has the Type II receiver. It had the Extreme Duty Scope Mount Factory installed. I also had the full length rail interface installed so there is a continuous rail the length of the rifle along with rails on the fore grip at 9:00, 3:00, and 6:00. A couple of other Items I purchased from DSA were the extended selector switch, which makes going from “fire” mode to “safe” mode reachable with your thumb, and the ERGO HK G3 style tactical sure grip which is basically a Hogue type grip. I replaced the stock Belgium type short flash hider with a Primary Weapons Systems FSC FAL which is a dual flash suppressor and compensator muzzle device. I purchased and installed a extended magazine catch from Arizona response System, which allows for easier magazine changes. I also have one of DSA’s standard molded front fore grips that I added a swivel sling mount to. Also included in the sale are all of the original parts that I replaced so the rifle can be put back to it stock configuration if desired.

So in this sale the buyer will receive; 1- DS ARMS SA58 FAL 18” Carbine, with the Extreme Duty Scope Mount, the full length rail interface, the original selector switch, extended selector switch,  the standard FAL pistol grip, tactical sure grip, Belgium short flash hider, PWS FSC FAL muzzle device, standard magazine catch, extended magazine catch, and extra DSA fore grip, one 20 round military surplus magazine, factory sling, factory hard case, original FN FAL manual, and DS ARM’s SA 58 owner’s manual. The optics and bi-pod in the pictures are NOT included in this sale.

This rifle is sold as is, and I cannot offer any warranty once it is paid for and leaves my possession. This will be a CASH ONLY sale. I will not ship this rifle, this will be a face to face sale. I will travel a reasonable distance to meet serious buyers. I will need to see a picture ID and the buyer will need to sign a bill of sale for my personal records.

I really appreciate your interest. If you have an offer, any questions or would like to see more pictures, please reply to this post.
I am not interested in trades at this time. 
Thank You

title: For Sale:  1986 BMW R-80 Airhead Cafe Racer
postcontent:
For sale is my 86 BMW r80rt mono-shock I have had a lot of work done to this bike and I have spent countless hours working on it to get it where it is at now.
This BMW is a mono-shock R80 so it is a single sided swing arm with the drive-shaft not a chain drive. It is very unique and rides excellent

I stripped the bike to just the engine and frame, I sent the tank, tail, fender and side covers off for a custom paint job. The pictures do no justice for paint, it is a custom gold with lots of pearl that really shows in the sunlight!
The frame was stripped to metal and repainted black with plenty of clear to make it really shine.
I cleaned the engine and drive-train and painted it with high temp engine paint.
The original tail light and signals were ditched for low profile signals and the tail light is off a 2008 Honda cbr 600rr, it is led and extremely bright.
The original handlebars were very tall and slightly bent so I replaced them with a set of black drag bars.
The original speedo and tach were not functional, I replaced them with a digital Acewell cluster that compliments the bike very well.
I replaced the exhaust with a single exit MAC full exhaust system that retains the center stand as well as the side stand!
It has brand new tires front and rear that have maybe 100 miles on them.
I have 2 seats one reupholstered in black and the other is an orange color needing to be recovered.
I replaced the restrictive intake box with 2 better flowing k&n cone filters.

There is so much that has been done to this bike, it is beautiful and I would prefer to keep it but I have not been able to work on it or ride it for over a year and I hate to see it just sitting in the garage not being appreciated like it should.
With the new intake system and exhaust I would suggest re-jetting the bike, I just have not had the ability to do so since I started my new job.
whoever gets this bike will for sure enjoy every second of it.

please email me with any questions or to set up a time to come see the bike.
No test rides without cash in my hand and a motorcycle endorsement on your license.
Possibly interested in trades, things that go bang plus cash, 4x4 trucks, fast cars, possibly other bikes... Let me know
